Here's an example script that demonstrates how to extract the author, creation date, and table information from a PDF file. Note that this script is a basic example and might need adjustments for handling various PDF formats and sizes.

```perl
#!/usr/bin/perl
use strict;
use warnings;
use PDF::API2;
use Text::Unidecode;

# Path to the PDF file
my $pdf_file = 'example.pdf';

# Open the PDF file
my $pdf = PDF::API2->open($pdf_file);

# Extract metadata (author, creation date)
my $info = $pdf->info;
my $author = $info->get('/Author')->as_utf8;
my $creation_date = $info->get('/CreationDate')->as_utf8;

# Extract table information
my $pages = $pdf->pages;
my @tables;

foreach my $page (1 .. $pages) {
    my $text = $pdf->page($page)->extract_text;
    push @tables, $text if $text =~ /\btable\s+(\d+)/i;  # Example regex to detect table number
}

# Output extracted information
print "Author: $author\n";
print "Creation Date: $creation_date\n";
print "Table Information:\n";
foreach my $table (@tables) {
    print "$table\n";
}

# Close the PDF file
$pdf->close;
```

